This paper is about improving the back-translation technique in neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses optimization and approximation techniques, which are common in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the proposed method involves sampling and restricted search space, which are relevant to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which is a common technique in the subfield of neural engineering (cs.NE).
